# RefineX Environment Variables

# ============================================
# CRITICAL: NEVER commit .env to Git!
# This file shows what variables are needed.
# Copy to .env and fill in real values.
# ============================================

# Node Environment
NODE_ENV=development

# ============================================
# ADMIN AUTHENTICATION
# ============================================

# Generate a secure 64-character random token
# PowerShell: -join ((48..57) + (65..90) + (97..122) | Get-Random -Count 64 | % {[char]$_})
# Linux/Mac: openssl rand -hex 32
#
# CRITICAL: 
# - Must be 32+ characters
# - Use different tokens for dev/staging/production
# - Rotate every 90 days
# - Never share or commit this token
ADMIN_TOKEN=

# ============================================
# DATABASE (if using real SQLite)
# ============================================

# Database file location (relative to project root)
DATABASE_PATH=./data/refinex.db

# ============================================
# RATE LIMITING
# ============================================

# Override default rate limits if needed
# (defaults are set in middleware.ts)
# RATE_LIMIT_ENTERPRISE=5
# RATE_LIMIT_WINDOW_MS=600000

# ============================================
# EMAIL (if adding email notifications)
# ============================================

# SMTP settings or service API key
# EMAIL_FROM=noreply@refinex.io
# RESEND_API_KEY=

# ============================================
# ANALYTICS (optional)
# ============================================

# Only add if you need analytics
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ANALYTICS_ID=

# ============================================
# SECURITY NOTES
# ============================================

# Rules for environment variables:
# 
# 1. SECRETS (passwords, tokens, API keys):
#    - NEVER prefix with NEXT_PUBLIC_
#    - Only accessible server-side
#    - Example: ADMIN_TOKEN, RESEND_API_KEY
#
# 2. PUBLIC CONFIG (safe to expose):
#    - Prefix with NEXT_PUBLIC_
#    - Accessible in browser
#    - Example: NEXT_PUBLIC_ANALYTICS_ID
#    - Never put secrets here!
#
# 3. WHAT TO NEVER PUT IN ENV:
#    - Customer data
#    - API keys for your customers
#    - Database credentials for customer DBs
#    - Anything that appears in your codebase examples
#
# 4. ROTATION SCHEDULE:
#    - Admin tokens: every 90 days
#    - API keys: every 180 days
#    - Service credentials: per service policy

# ============================================
# PRODUCTION CHECKLIST
# ============================================

# Before deploying to production:
# [ ] Generated new admin token (not the dev one)
# [ ] Verified ADMIN_TOKEN is 64+ characters
# [ ] Checked no secrets in Git history
# [ ] Enabled HTTPS (middleware auto-adds HSTS)
# [ ] Tested admin auth works
# [ ] Verified rate limiting works
# [ ] Removed debug console.logs
# [ ] Checked CSP doesn't break site
